/past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/20180120_210100-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"maxine anderson san francisco pole and dance\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Max is originally from Miami, Florida and her fitness background bloomed with martial arts. She started pole dancing just two years ago and fell in love with both pole and aerials. She loves the spirit of the pole community and has found a home amongst a group of strong personalities of all shapes sizes and ages with a passion for self-expression and continued learning. Putting that self expression on a stage, Max competed in Pacific Pole Championships in 2016 and continues to train for her next competition at Golden Gate Pole Championships in February 2018.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>She teaches lyra, pole, and is an epic bachelorette party host at SF Pole and Dance.</div>','Maxine Anderson','','inherit','closed','closed','','1891-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-22 20:58:51','2018-01-22 20:58:51','',1891,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/1891-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2996,1,'2018-01-21 20:04:17','2018-01-21 20:04:17','','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','1873-revision-v1','','','2018-01-21 20:04:17','2018-01-21 20:04:17','',1873,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/1873-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2997,2,'2018-01-22 20:58:02','2018-01-22 20:58:02','','20180120_210100','','inherit','open','closed','','20180120_210100','','','2018-01-22 20:58:27','2018-01-22 20:58:27','',1891,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/20180120_210100.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2998,2,'2018-01-22 21:24:08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2999\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-07-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Amy Bond, San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAmy Bond is the owner and founder of San Francisco Pole and Dance. She has been competing in PSO level events since 2012, when she entered her first competition and did a back walkover right off the stage! Amy has been teaching pole and aerial for over 4 years and opened San Francisco Pole and Dance in May, 2016.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAmy has competed in 8 competitions to date. She is the 2016 semi-pro Pole Theatre Pole Comedy division winner, and also competed in the 2017 Pole Theatre Pole Comedy professional division. She has performed around San Francisco in everything from So You Think You Can Lapdance, where she won season III, episode 7 and won second in the season III finale, to Grace Cathedral in San Francisco.\r\n\r\nShe teaches pole, lyra, aerial silks, gymnastics, and sexy choreography. When asked which one she likes the most, it\'s the artistic and performance side of pole dancing. She can\'t wait to share it with you!','Amy Bond','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-22 21:24:08','2018-01-22 21:24:08','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=2998',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(2999,2,'2018-01-22 21:10:34','2018-01-22 21:10:34','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 07','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-07','','','2018-01-22 21:10:48','2018-01-22 21:10:48','',2998,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-07.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3000,2,'2018-01-23 02:21:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3004\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2016-06-11-SFPD-Headshot-Web-11-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Kimmy Fitz San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nKimmy Fitz has been pole dancing since 2010, when she started dancing at Poletential, now <a href=\"https://www.inspirationstudios.com/\">Inpsiration Studios. </a>Kimmy started competing in 2013 at PSO\'s L2 Championship division. She now competes at the Pro level and has two national pro titles - Pro Artist Nationals 2nd place in 2015, and Pro Artistic Nationals 2nd place in 2016. She also won 2nd place at the first Golden Gate Pole Championships Women\'s pro division in 2017. Beyond pole dancing, Kimmy enjoys wrapping people in sparkly elastic through her company, <a href=\"https://www.etsy.com/market/ruby_by_kimb\">Ruby by Kim B</a>.','Kimmy','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-23 02:21:34','2018-01-23 02:21:34','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3000',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3001,1,'2018-01-22 21:30:53','2018-01-22 21:30:53','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-2999\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-07-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Amy Bond, San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAmy Bond is the owner and founder of San Francisco Pole and Dance. She has been competing in PSO level events since 2012, when she entered her first competition and did a back walkover right off the stage! Amy has been teaching pole and aerial for over 4 years and opened San Francisco Pole and Dance in May, 2016.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAmy has competed in 8 competitions to date. She is the 2016 semi-pro Pole Theatre Pole Comedy division winner, and also competed in the 2017 Pole Theatre Pole Comedy professional division. She has performed around San Francisco in everything from So You Think You Can Lapdance, where she won season III, episode 7 and won second in the season III finale, to Grace Cathedral in San Francisco.\r\n\r\nShe teaches pole, lyra, aerial silks, gymnastics, and sexy choreography. When asked which one she likes the most, it\'s the artistic and performance side of pole dancing. She can\'t wait to share it with you!','Amy Bond','','inherit','closed','closed','','2998-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-22 21:30:53','2018-01-22 21:30:53','',2998,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/2998-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3002,2,'2018-01-23 01:14:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-23 01:14:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&p=3002',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3003,2,'2018-01-23 02:33:33','2018-01-23 02:33:33','Kaila Prins, also known as burlesque dancer DeeDee Queen, is a drag queen trapped in a cis-woman’s body — a performing woman who is performing “woman.” She is a burlesque, pole, and drag artist who teaches burlesque and storytelling and co-produces Curtains Cabaret, a theatrical burlesque company in Redwood City. She recently developed and produced a feminist one-woman burlesque show, which she workshopped at Feinstein\'s/54 Below in New York City and premiered in Redwood City. (She will be reviving the show in San Francisco in 2018.) She teaches theatre in San Jose and will be performing in several musicals in 2018.\r\n\r\nKaila has been seen at the California Burlypicks (2016/17), Hawaii Burlesque Festival (2016/17), Vermont Burlesque Festival (2017), Great Burlesque Expo (2017), Freezing Tassel in Alaska (2017), Philadelphia Burlesque Festival (2017), Hollywood Burlesque Festival (2017), Oregon Burlesque Festival (2017), Hawaii Burlesque Festival (2017), and the Amsterdam Burlesque Awards (2017).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://performingwoman.com\">Performing Woman</a> (personal brand)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://siliconvalleyburlesque.com\">Silicon Valley Burlesque</a> (business)','Kaila Prins','','inherit','closed','closed','','2848-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-23 02:33:33','2018-01-23 02:33:33','',2848,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/2848-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3004,2,'2018-01-23 02:20:51','2018-01-23 02:20:51','','2016-06-11 - SFPD - Headshot - Web - 11','','inherit','open','closed','','2016-06-11-sfpd-headshot-web-11','','','2018-01-23 02:21:04','2018-01-23 02:21:04','',3000,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2016-06-11-SFPD-Headshot-Web-11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3005,2,'2018-01-24 22:14:02','2018-01-24 22:14:02','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3006\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-25-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Nate James San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nNate James began his journey as a self-taught student of the world, chasing dreams of grandeur! His experience is primarily in aerial and flexibility, however he has ADHD and finds other circus disciplines and extra curricular activities that keep him well rounded in his practice. He has a well rounded background, as well, from opera and musical theater, to drag and improv, to fully fledged circus freak working as a free lance artist, and for a small touring company. He moved to Budapest, HU for a year to pursue his dreams, and studied, taught, and performed aerial at the National Circus School of Hungary. He most recently finished a contract as an aerialist with Cirque du Soleil in the DR.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCurrently he is in the Bay Area and training and creating!!!\r\n\r\nHe’s excited to share with, and learn from you!','Nate James','','publish','closed','closed','','nate-james','','','2018-01-24 22:14:02','2018-01-24 22:14:02','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3005',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3006,2,'2018-01-23 02:34:35','2018-01-23 02:34:35','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 25','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-25','','','2018-01-23 02:34:51','2018-01-23 02:34:51','',3005,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-25.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3007,2,'2018-01-23 02:46:04','2018-01-23 02:46:04','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3009\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-15-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Christine Lee San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nChristine has been training, performing and teaching circus arts over 12 years. She specializes in Single Point Trapeze, Aerial Hoop, Flying Trapeze, Double Aerial, and contortion/acrobatics. Christine has taught/performed at various resorts in the Caribbean and South East Asia, and has been teaching and performing in San Francisco over the past 7 years. She\'s passionate about circus arts, always experimenting with new apparatuses, and loves sharing her passion for circus with students.','Christine Lee','','publish','closed','closed','','christine-lee','','','2018-01-23 02:46:04','2018-01-23 02:46:04','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3007',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3008,2,'2018-01-23 02:42:21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Allison Hudson grew up in Houston, Texas and moved to the Bay Area in 2010. She loves singing, pole dancing, teaching pole and spending time with her beloved friends and family. She has been a competitive athlete all of her life in swimming, soccer, golf and cheerleading and discovered pole dancing at age 32 after having her first born son and gaining 60 pounds that wouldn\'t come off.','Allison Hudson','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-23 02:42:21','2018-01-23 02:42:21','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3008',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3009,2,'2018-01-23 02:38:10','2018-01-23 02:38:10','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 15','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-15','','','2018-01-23 02:38:28','2018-01-23 02:38:28','',3007,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-15.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3010,2,'2018-01-26 21:21:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Yoko Taketani has been a classical ballerina from the age of six. She began pole dance training at Studio Polish, Tokyo, in 2009, and has been instructing since 2010. Yoko\'s pole performances include Pole Dance All Stars 2013, Japan Pole Exhibition 2014; Miss Pole Dance Japan 2012&amp;2014; US National Championship 2013; Pole Theatre Sydney 2014; Pole Classic at Pole Expo 2015; Pole Theatre Japan 2015 Guest Performance and the Felix Cane Pole Championships 2015. She teaches L3 and L4 as well as contemporary choreography at SFPD.','Yoko Taketani','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-26 21:21:24','2018-01-26 21:21:24','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3010',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3011,2,'2018-01-23 02:50:53','2018-01-23 02:50:53','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3012\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-06-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Alyssa Fong Instructor at San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAlyssa is a San Francisco native and started dancing in 2008 in freestyle hip hop, specifically waacking and voguing. She practiced it for four years, and it was there that she learned to enjoy using music as a tool to express herself through movement.   Her first pole class was at Studio Botan in 2014, and she fell in love with the strength and elegance of the dance as well as how accepting the community was.\r\n\r\nShe tried her first lyra class in late 2016 and and it was love at first pike. With teaching, she hopes to show students the freedom of expressing themselves through movement and learn that their dance is unique to themselves which is a beautiful thing.','Alyssa Fong','','publish','closed','closed','','alyssa-fong','','','2018-01-23 02:51:52','2018-01-23 02:51:52','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3011',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3012,2,'2018-01-23 02:47:57','2018-01-23 02:47:57','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 06','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-06','','','2018-01-23 02:48:16','2018-01-23 02:48:16','',3011,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-06.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3013,2,'2018-01-23 03:00:49','2018-01-23 03:00:49','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3015\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-24-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"San Francisco Pole and Dance instructor Carlie LeDuc\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nCarlie has been pole dancing since 2012. As someone who has always wanted to fly, pole is the closest experience she has come to it! She has competed in 4 PSO events, medaling in Pacific Pole Championships 2015 &amp; Nationals 2016. Her dance style is eclectic with a background in West African, Salsa, and Modern dance.\r\n\r\nCarlie loves the way pole has given her greater confidence and pride in her body and she loves sharing that with others!','Carlie Leduc','','publish','closed','closed','','carlie-leduc','','','2018-01-23 03:02:21','2018-01-23 03:02:21','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3013',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3014,2,'2018-01-23 03:01:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Michelle fell in love with contortion style flexibility as a way to tone and shape the body. She started stretching as an adult, and with regular practice, went from a tall triangle to beautifully flat square splits in only 6 months time! She loves to share what she has learned and see her students make progress. Michelle will guide you through splits and back flexibility work, provide gentle pushing to square and deepen your splits and help you develop technique through a standardized set of contortion warm ups and drills that will help you get ready to bend!','Michelle Cooper','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-23 03:01:34','2018-01-23 03:01:34','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3014',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3015,2,'2018-01-23 02:54:56','2018-01-23 02:54:56','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 24','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-24','','','2018-01-23 02:55:13','2018-01-23 02:55:13','',3013,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-24.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3016,2,'2018-01-23 03:02:27','2018-01-23 03:02:27','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3015\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-24-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"San Francisco Pole and Dance instructor Carlie LeDuc\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nCarlie has been pole dancing since 2012. As someone who has always wanted to fly, pole is the closest experience she has come to it! She has competed in 4 PSO events, medaling in Pacific Pole Championships 2015 &amp; Nationals 2016. Her dance style is eclectic with a background in West African, Salsa, and Modern dance.\r\n\r\nCarlie loves the way pole has given her greater confidence and pride in her body and she loves sharing that with others!','Carlie Leduc','','inherit','closed','closed','','3013-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-23 03:02:27','2018-01-23 03:02:27','',3013,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3013-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3017,2,'2018-01-23 03:16:18','2018-01-23 03:16:18','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3019\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-12-246x300.jpg\" alt=\"Karri Mae Becker San Francisco Pole and Dance instructor\" width=\"246\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nALWAYS SHOOT FOR THE STARS. IF YOU FALL SHORT AT LEAST YOU HAVE MADE IT TO THE MOON! -KARRI MAE BECKER\r\n\r\nAs an NASM Certified Personal Trainer and ACE Certified Group Fitness Instructor, Karri taught several different class formats in fitness centers in across Northern Virginia and San Francisco. As an extension of her fitness training Karri was introduced to pole fitness 9 years ago and quickly became dedicated to the sport of pole fitness.\r\n\r\nShe has been teaching and performing pole fitness for over 8 years and opened her own pole fitness studio - Pole Pressure® of Leesburg in 2009. Karri owned a successful Pole Pressure® Studio in Northern Virginia for 4 years before closing its doors to relocate to San Francisco where she continues to spread the love of pole. Currently, Karri is a Regional Group Fitness Manager for Crunch Gyms in San Francisco as well as an aerial instructor for SF Pole and Dance and Poletential. In addition, Karri has the following ventures...\r\n\r\nFounder, <a href=\"http://www.Cirq-fit.com\">CirqFIT Aerial Instructor Certification </a>\r\n\r\nFounder, <a href=\"http://www.AerialArtsAssoc.com\">Aerial Arts Association</a>\r\n\r\nFounder, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/aerialhooptricks/\">Aerial Hoop Tricks</a>\r\n\r\nWhen Karri was introduced to Pole Fitness she was 30 lbs overweight and and a self proclaimed “Insecure Wallflower”. Karri’s favorite part about teaching pole fitness is fostering the same changes in her students that she personally experienced while seeing them develop both physical and inner strength!\r\n\r\nKarri has won the following titles:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>2017 1st Place Winner Pole Sport Organization - Dramatic Level 4</li>\r\n 	<li>2012 Peoples Choice Champion, Pole Dance America</li>\r\n 	<li>2011 Miss South Carolina Pole Champion</li>\r\n 	<li>Pole Dance America 2011 Miss Echo Award</li>\r\n 	<li>Pole Dance America 2011 Miss Technical Award</li>\r\n 	<li>Pole Dance America</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nKarri has the following fitness certifications:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>NASM Personal Trainer Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>ACE Group Fitness Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Zumba Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Aqua Zumba Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>BASI Pilates Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>YogaFit Certification Pound Fitness Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Schwinn Spinning Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Les Mills BodyPump Certified Instructor</li>\r\n 	<li>Les Mills BodyCombat Certified Instructor</li>\r\n 	<li>Les Mills BodyAttack Certified Instructor</li>\r\n 	<li>Les Mills CX Worx Certified Instructor</li>\r\n 	<li>Urban Kickbox Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Urban KicksAss Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Pon de Flow Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>DISQ Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>AntiGravity Yoga Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>AntiGravity AirBarre Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>HoopnoticaFIT Certified Instructor</li>\r\n 	<li>HoopnoticaFLOW Certified Instructor</li>\r\n 	<li>Vertical Dance Instructor Certification</li>\r\n 	<li>Discoveries Dance Instructor Certification</li>\r\n</ul>','Karri Mae Becker','','publish','closed','closed','','karri-mae-becker','','','2018-01-23 03:16:18','2018-01-23 03:16:18','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3017',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3018,2,'2018-01-23 03:30:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Janet has been a dancer her entire life and studied ballet, tap, jazz, hip hop, lyrical and contemporary dance since the age of 3. She fell in love with pole and aerial in 2010 and has taught at various studios in Los Angeles and the Bay Area. She loves translating the art of dance onto aerial apparatuses. Her classes focus on technique, quality of movement, and most of all how to have fun up in the air!','Janet Casamento','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-23 03:30:32','2018-01-23 03:30:32','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3018',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3019,2,'2018-01-23 03:04:12','2018-01-23 03:04:12','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 12','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-12','','','2018-01-23 03:05:56','2018-01-23 03:05:56','',3017,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-12.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3020,2,'2018-01-23 03:40:33','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Elyse is a hip hoppin’, hair tossin’, body rollin’, high energy style pole dancer! And her background is definitely all of that.\r\n\r\nShe’s practiced a wide variety of dance forms from the sensual Argentine tango to the flips and dips of country swing. But, her strongest experience comes from formal dance teams. Not only did she dance for her high school and university teams but, she’s also was a pro dancer for the AFL\'s Dallas Vigilantes and has performed at American Airlines center and with the Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders at the new Cowboys Stadium. After moving to SF, she made the final round of auditions for the Golden State Warriors dance team which led her to a spot on Vanity Dance, a high-heeled hiphop dance company.\r\n\r\nAs a pole dancer, Elyse began training in late 2009 when she took her first pole class. Training quickly turned to teaching in 2010 and she continues to teach all over the Bay Area today. Thats 7 years teaching!\r\n\r\nHer pole teaching expertise is in body technique, big &amp; momentous twirl combos, LA style choreo, and strength moves. She’s won a couple titles at PSO’s Southern Pole and Pacific Pole Championships. Performances include Miss Texas Pole Star, SF’s Volare Variety, Dance Filthy USA, and is on her third PoleShow LA.\r\n\r\nPersonal site: <a class=\"_ng0lj\" href=\"http://l.instagram.com/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.movewithme.co%2F&amp;e=ATPe4GCjvKLnrHs63Qo10f-D7iEZDbPuq3GTMReGdz_DYQMSD7paiEBT8DDBuLBpziVx21gDaj_wVEfqWMoFmZRZxfBQySM\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow me noopener noreferrer\">www.movewithme.co</a>','Elyse Ogara','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-23 03:40:33','2018-01-23 03:40:33','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3020',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3021,2,'2018-01-23 17:35:19','2018-01-23 17:35:19','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3022\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-05-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Jody Ryker San Francisco Pole and Dance Instructor\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nJody trained in many different athletic disciplines including rollerblading, weight lifting, and dance before beginning pole dance in 2011. She immediately knew she had finally found the right art form to express herself. Since then, Jody has branched out into other circus arts including aerial hoop and acrobatics. Jody performs around northern California at music festivals, night clubs, and circus shows. She teaches pole dance and aerial hoop at UCSC and SF Pole &amp; Dance. Jody also graduated with a master\'s in pure mathematics and teaches math at Foothill College.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHer dance group is called <a href=\"http://www.polediversity.com\">Pole Diversity, available for bookings!</a>','Jody Ryker','','publish','closed','closed','','jody-ryker','','','2018-01-23 17:35:19','2018-01-23 17:35:19','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3021',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3022,2,'2018-01-23 17:33:50','2018-01-23 17:33:50','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 05','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-05','','','2018-01-23 17:34:14','2018-01-23 17:34:14','',3021,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-05.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3023,2,'2018-01-23 18:58:15','2018-01-23 18:58:15','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3022\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-05-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Jody Ryker San Francisco Pole and Dance Instructor\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nJody trained in many different athletic disciplines including rollerblading, weight lifting, and dance before beginning pole dance in 2011. She immediately knew she had finally found the right art form to express herself. Since then, Jody has branched out into other circus arts including aerial hoop and acrobatics. Jody performs around northern California at music festivals, night clubs, and circus shows. She teaches pole dance and aerial hoop at UCSC and SF Pole &amp; Dance. Jody also graduated with a master\'s in pure mathematics and teaches math at Foothill College.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHer dance group is called <a href=\"http://www.polediversity.com\">Pole Diversity, available for bookings!</a>','Jody Ryker','','inherit','closed','closed','','3021-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-23 18:58:15','2018-01-23 18:58:15','',3021,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3021-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3025,2,'2018-01-24 02:30:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Perfect what you learned in L1, while also incorporating leg hangs, cupid, basic invert, and climbing variations into your pole dance lexicon. We\'ll begin to build the foundation for intermediate pole moves such as butterfly, shoulder mount, and caterpillar climbs. Pre-requisite: Ability to climb to the top of the pole.','L2 - Beginner Plus','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:30:32','2018-01-24 02:30:32','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3025',0,'gym_class','',0),(3026,2,'2018-01-24 02:31:58','0000-00-00 00:00:00','L3 is meant for students who have been taking L2 for a little while, but want to push themselves to work on progressions for L3 tricks. Students should be able to perform a clean inversion off of the floor, and be ready to work on shoulder mounts. The instructor will break down pre-advanced tricks into small pieces so that advanced beginners and intermediate students alike will receive progressions.','L3 (Adv. Beg./Int.)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:31:58','2018-01-24 02:31:58','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3026',0,'gym_class','',0),(3027,2,'2018-01-24 02:17:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:17:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&p=3027',0,'gym_class','',0),(3028,2,'2018-01-24 02:32:17','0000-00-00 00:00:00','L4 is meant for the intermediate-advanced level pole student. You should be able to do a clean shoulder mount from the ground and be working on aerial shoulder mount and aerial inversions. We will also condition handspring variations from the ground.','L4 - Int/Adv.','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:32:17','2018-01-24 02:32:17','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3028',0,'gym_class','',0),(3029,2,'2018-01-24 02:36:41','0000-00-00 00:00:00','L5 is our most advanced level and students tend to have multiple years of pole under their belts. In order to join L5, you should feel comfortable performing an aerial shoulder mount, backbend hold on the ground and a handspring hold. L5 students will focus on lines, combination creation, and advanced level tricks.','L5 - Advanced (Pre-Professional)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:36:41','2018-01-24 02:36:41','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3029',0,'gym_class','',0),(3030,2,'2018-01-24 02:29:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:29:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&p=3030',0,'gym_class','',0),(3031,2,'2018-01-24 02:40:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Build a solid foundation for your aerial journey. Inversions Bootcamp is the bridge class between L1 and L2. We will work on climbs, inverts and knee hangs while focusing on technique and building endurance. This class is for anyone who wants to solidify their aerial basics.','Inversions Bootcamp','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:40:44','2018-01-24 02:40:44','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3031',0,'gym_class','',0),(3032,2,'2018-01-24 02:41:44','0000-00-00 00:00:00','(Re) discover the bottom third of the pole in this low pole class. So often, we jump over the lower third in order to perform death defying drops and tricks. In this low pole class, we\'ll explore movement such as spins, floorwork, handstands and more, redefining the use of the lower third.','Low Pole','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:41:44','2018-01-24 02:41:44','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3032',0,'gym_class','',0),(3033,2,'2018-01-24 02:44:30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Learn new choreography to the songs that you love the most! This class is open level, but not for first time pole students. Here, we focus on infusing your tricks routine with new floorwork, spins and body waves. Dance styles include contemporary, hip hop, lyrical and ballet-inspired. Feel free to bring your favorite pair of heels for this class, some knee pads and leg warmers or borrow from the studio.','Pole Choreography (All Levels)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:44:30','2018-01-24 02:44:30','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3033',0,'gym_class','',0),(3034,2,'2018-01-24 02:45:59','0000-00-00 00:00:00','During this class you will learn a choreographed dance routine in a dynamic, thready, and sultry style. This class will help you learn leg waves, thread throughs, weaves and floor twists and drop splits. We will focus on combining sexy choreography in heels. Learn to slink and slither! Heels and knee pads are strongly encouraged.','Sexy Choreography','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:45:59','2018-01-24 02:45:59','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3034',0,'gym_class','',0),(3035,2,'2018-01-24 02:47:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Pull out your pins! We\'ll work on progressions of spin pole movements in this class. Whether you are learning basic spin inversions and flow or practicing your latest flip trick, this class is multi-level. In each class, we\'ll learn a small combo combining an ascent, trick, transition and descent that we\'ll dance out at the end of class.','Spin Pole (Mixed Level)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:47:11','2018-01-24 02:47:11','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3035',0,'gym_class','',0),(3036,2,'2018-01-24 02:49:35','0000-00-00 00:00:00','This aerial silks class is for everyone from first timers to intermediate students! In this class, we\'ll begin with conditioning movement on the ground and on the silks, work flexibility and then hop on the silks to learn climbing skills, inversion foundations and 2-3 new tricks in the air. Please wear leggings and a bodysuit or a shirt that you can tuck into your pants.','Aerial Silks - Beginners','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:49:35','2018-01-24 02:49:35','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3036',0,'gym_class','',0),(3037,2,'2018-01-24 02:50:38','0000-00-00 00:00:00','This aerial silks class is for intermediate students! In this class, you\'ll build upon foundations learned in the beginner class and begin to work on drops, rolls and intermediate movement such as wheeldowns, beats, and teardrop climb.\r\n\r\nPlease wear leggings and a bodysuit or a shirt that you can tuck into your pants.','Aerial Silks - Intermediate','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:50:38','2018-01-24 02:50:38','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3037',0,'gym_class','',0),(3038,2,'2018-01-24 02:52:06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','The lyra is a large metal aerial hoop that hangs about 5 feet off of the ground. This class is designed for people who are brand new to lyra. The main focus of the class is to help students build strength and flexibility to properly mount the lyra and maintain balance through core conditioning and active flexibility exercises. Additionally, students will learn to invert and move through various low bar poses in the lyra such as Lady on the Moon, Mermaid, Posse, Arabesque, and many more. Progressions will be offered as students master each pose!\r\n\r\nAttire: Please wear yoga pants, a tank top, and socks to make sure your body is covered during the class.','Intro to Lyra: (Beginner/L1)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:52:06','2018-01-24 02:52:06','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3038',0,'gym_class','',0),(3039,2,'2018-01-24 02:53:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','In level 2, students will continue building core strength and flexibility and begin learning more advanced mounts and poses. We will explore balancing in the hoop, and move through splits, drops, and rolls. Students will also begin working on poses on the high bar. Students may also try poses on a spinning lyra. This class is appropriate for students who can properly invert low bar and are comfortable with all the basic mounts.\r\n\r\nAttire: Please wear yoga pants, a tank top, and socks to make sure your body is covered during the class.','Intermediate Lyra: (L2)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:53:11','2018-01-24 02:53:11','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3039',0,'gym_class','',0),(3040,2,'2018-01-24 02:56:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','In level 3, students will incorporate dance and choreography in their movements and work on smooth execution of more advanced poses, transitions and combinations on both high and low bar. Students will also practice combinations and movements involving momentum and may also work through movements on a spinning lyra. This class is appropriate for students who can properly invert low and high bar.\r\n\r\nAttire: Please wear yoga pants, a tank top, and socks to make sure your body is covered during the class.','Advanced Lyra: (L3)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:56:24','2018-01-24 02:56:24','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3040',0,'gym_class','',0),(3041,2,'2018-01-24 02:57:28','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Dust off those heels and strap yourself into the Hotttt Seat as you transform your metal chair into a sturdy partner. This floorwork-based chair dance class is sure to get you conditioned and learning new choreography. Stick with it each week, as we build choreographed dance and flow to a new song every few weeks. Knee pads are recommended.','Hottt Seat! (All Levels Chair Class)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:57:28','2018-01-24 02:57:28','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3041',0,'gym_class','',0),(3042,2,'2018-01-24 02:58:51','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Newbies welcome! In this class, we will progressively build foundational skills for a solid and comfortable handstand. Using partner drills and solo work, students will increase the flexibility and strength necessary for finding a stable handstand line. As students get more comfortable on their hands, we will begin to add creative movement to increase their stability and confidence in a variety of handstand shapes. Students who can comfortably hold a handstand will work on presses, more challenging shapes, and other dynamic entrances into handstand. This is the perfect class if you are working on your handstand or trying to build the skills for a solid handstand!','Intro to Handstands','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 02:58:51','2018-01-24 02:58:51','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3042',0,'gym_class','',0),(3043,2,'2018-01-24 03:00:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Our flexibility classes follow a beginner\'s contortion style of training. <strong>This is not a yoga flow.</strong> In this class, we will train active and passive flexibility starting with a hip opening warm up, moving into side splits and straddle work and finish with 15 minutes of dedicate back bending. This is an all levels class from first timers to intermediate students. We\'ll work on beginner contortion poses like stag split, standing split and more.','Flexibility Training (All Levels)','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 03:00:18','2018-01-24 03:00:18','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3043',0,'gym_class','',0),(3044,2,'2018-01-24 03:03:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div>\r\nBump and grind your way to body positivity in this all-levels burlesque class, where you’ll learn the fundamentals of striptease and classic burlesque dance. In each class, you’ll learn different skills through choreography while learning how to take it all off (well, maybe not all!).</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Whether you want to become a performer or just want to feel good in the skin you’re in, this all-levels class will show you how to shake your jiggly bits and show off your assets like a pro. Burlesque fundamentals may include: bumps, grinds, shimmies, shakes, striptease, basic chair work, floor work, prop work, tassel twirling, and more.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>','Burlesque','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-01-24 03:03:07','2018-01-24 03:03:07','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_class&#038;p=3044',0,'gym_class','',0),(3045,2,'2018-01-25 03:01:31','2018-01-25 03:01:31','Mikal started his pole journey 2 years ago after a New Year\'s resolution brought him stumbling into classes with SFPD\'s Karri Becker, and fell in love instantly with the unique combination of dance, gymnastics, and fitness. Hours of classes, performances, and competitions later, Mikal is excited to share his childlike energy and excitement for pole &amp; dance with SFPD. Coming from a background of dance (hip-hop, contemporary, ballroom) and a brief stint in gymnastics, he is thrilled to sweat and laugh with the SFPD team &amp; students.','Mikal','','publish','closed','closed','','mikal','','','2018-01-25 03:09:02','2018-01-25 03:09:02','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3045',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3046,2,'2018-01-24 22:16:02','2018-01-24 22:16:02','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3047\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-20-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Shelly Ann Instructor at San Francisco Pole and Dance\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nShelly has been an instructor for over 4 years and has taught at Miami Pole Dance (FL), Boston Pole Fitness (MA) and Allure in Los Angeles (CA). She has taken workshops with Felix Cane, Alethea Austin, Pantera, Jenyne Butterfly and other elite pole athletes in an effort to improve the way she teaches and learns. Shelly’s motto is centered on “progress not perfection” and respects that everyone’s journey toward their fitness goal is different.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Shelly Ann','','publish','closed','closed','','shelly-ann','','','2018-01-25 03:21:29','2018-01-25 03:21:29','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3046',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3047,2,'2018-01-24 22:15:42','2018-01-24 22:15:42','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 20','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-20','','','2018-01-24 22:15:57','2018-01-24 22:15:57','',3046,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-20.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3048,2,'2018-01-24 22:16:36','2018-01-24 22:16:36','Seanmichael is an international performance artist with a penchant for rotational inertia and a rebellious attitude toward gravity. With an ethereal movement quality and otherworldly command of rigid aerial apparatuses like pole and cube, his work has been described by humans as “extraterrestrial ballet” and by extraterrestrials as “not too bad.” Seanmichael has been a stage explorer for more than 27 years with recent notable engagements including an aerial performance in Britney Spears\' music video \"Make Me,\" performing alongside famed DJ, Moby, a residency at The Galaxy Resort in Macau, and as a principle cast member in The Vespertine Circus, in San Francisco. He is a founding member of Flux Vertical Theater and Manarchy Male Revue.\r\n\r\nPersonal site: https://www.seanmichaelpolaris.com/','Sean Michael Rau','','publish','closed','closed','','sean-michael-rau','','','2018-01-25 03:00:55','2018-01-25 03:00:55','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3048',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3049,2,'2018-01-24 22:17:05','2018-01-24 22:17:05','Sylphie is a San Francisco based performing artist and instructor. She began her training in Vaganova Ballet at the age of three. On her pursuit for a career as a dancer, she stumbled upon circus arts through her elementary school\'s circus program, Circus Waldissima. Shortly after, she began training circus professionally at the San Francisco Circus Center under the tutelage of Elena Panova and Serchmaa Byamba, and was part of the Professional Aerial Program Created by Elena Panova in 2006. Since graduating in 2008, Sylphie has been performing and teaching internationally as a circus artist and dancer.','Sylphie Currin','','publish','closed','closed','','sylphie-currin','','','2018-01-25 03:24:57','2018-01-25 03:24:57','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3049',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3050,2,'2018-01-24 22:18:14','2018-01-24 22:18:14','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3051\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-09-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Tiffany Rose Mockler San Francisco Pole and Dance Instructor\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nTiffany Rose Mockler is a former National Champion for Synchronized Swimming and found Pole Dance in 2010. She has competed and performed around the world. She is the current Pole Championship Series Silver Medalist and a cast member in Tonya Kay\'s Pin Up Pole Show in Los Angeles. She is also a online instructor for Cleo\'s Rockin\' Pole and teaches in both Northern and Southern California. She loves sharing the art of Pole dance with others.','Tiffany Rose Mockler','','publish','closed','closed','','tiffany-rose-mockler','','','2018-01-25 03:37:40','2018-01-25 03:37:40','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3050',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3051,2,'2018-01-24 22:17:47','2018-01-24 22:17:47','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 09','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-09','','','2018-01-24 22:18:06','2018-01-24 22:18:06','',3050,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-09.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3052,2,'2018-01-24 22:19:43','2018-01-24 22:19:43','Andrey Pfening was born on March 11th, 1990 in Samarkand, Uzbekistan. He spent his childhood in Samara, Russia, and at the age of 12 moved to US and has resided in San Francisco Bay Area ever since.\r\n\r\nWhile in high school, Andrey came across a youtube video of David Belle (co-founder of parkour) and instantly was drawn to the activity and began seeking out knowledge and experience. He practiced with friends and then dedicated himself to training on his own several days a week. As he gained proficiency, others were drawn to his abilities and in turn attracted to his teachings.\r\nAndrey has become a recognizable member of the parkour community. He helps orchestrate local monthly jams in San Francisco and is committed to educating himself about parkour and the most effective teaching tools. He frequently attends local and national parkour summits, with well known practitioners, which review the most up to date trends in the discipline, which he implements into his teachings.\r\n\r\nAfter several years of being involved in parkour community Andrey began his teaching career at two fitness facilities, Athletic Playground and The Cave. Parkour was his main subject, and as time went on Andrey’s interests spread to handstand balancing, acrobatics, crossfit, and gymnastic strength training.\r\n\r\nOutside of the gym, Andrey spends a lot of time coming up with skill progressions, class outlines and visual aids which assist his physical and vocal style of teaching. He uses video of himself and his own students to break down skills, frame by frame.\r\nAnnually Andrey performs in live performances, working with local and international choreographers. In 2015 and 2016 he had a rare opportunity to be part of two SF Opera productions “The Trojans” and \"Carmen.\" He also periodically choreographs and performs pieces of his own.','Andre Pfennig','','publish','closed','closed','','andre-pfennig','','','2018-01-25 03:17:05','2018-01-25 03:17:05','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3052',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3053,2,'2018-01-24 22:20:15','2018-01-24 22:20:15','Max teaches Pole and Lyra and is a certified CirqFIT instructor, which is a Lyra instructor training program. She has a background in accounting and finance and is the Financial Manager of Aerial Arts Association. She is also passionate about health and fitness through aerial arts, especially making them accessible to every body.','Maxine Anderson','','publish','closed','closed','','maxine-anderson','','','2018-01-25 01:43:00','2018-01-25 01:43:00','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3053',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3054,2,'2018-01-24 22:21:21','2018-01-24 22:21:21','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3055\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-03-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Joshua Aurora San Francisco Pole and Dance instructor\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAurora has studied dance, yoga, and martial arts for most of their life. Aurora trained in ballet, jazz, and contemporary dance including summer programs with the Northern California Ballet and California State Summer School for the Arts. Aurora started teaching yoga and dance when they were 18 and has continued to do so intermittently for the last ten years while running an acupuncture, meditation, and energy healing practice. They also return frequently to their home dance studio in South Lake Tahoe to teach young dancers safe alignment, tricks, and AcroYoga. Aurora performs neo burlesque and pole in the Bay Area.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Josh/Aurora','','publish','closed','closed','','josh-aurora','','','2018-01-25 03:22:07','2018-01-25 03:22:07','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3054',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3055,2,'2018-01-24 22:21:03','2018-01-24 22:21:03','','2017-12-29 - SFPD Headshots - 03','','inherit','open','closed','','2017-12-29-sfpd-headshots-03','','','2018-01-24 22:21:18','2018-01-24 22:21:18','',3054,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-03.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3056,2,'2018-01-24 22:22:37','2018-01-24 22:22:37','','Image uploaded from iOS','','inherit','open','closed','','image-uploaded-from-ios','','','2018-01-24 22:23:18','2018-01-24 22:23:18','',2848,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Image-uploaded-from-iOS.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3057,2,'2018-01-24 22:23:50','2018-01-24 22:23:50','Colleen started her aerial career at the Philadelphia School of Circus Arts training fabric, rope, trapeze and lyra. Throughout her time in Philadelphia she would frequent California to train at various circus schools to broaden her scope of learning. This practice allowed her to gain versatility in her aerial movement, something she still presently values. Much like Colleen herself, her classes are playful and focus on the beauty of body movement. Having a love for performing, she structures her class in a way where students are learning fundamental aerial moves, all while gaining the confidence to turn them into sequences. Her mission as an instructor and human being is to create a judge free environment where students are excited and comfortable exploring new types of movement.','Colleen Dixon','','publish','closed','closed','','colleen-dixon','','','2018-01-25 03:51:20','2018-01-25 03:51:20','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?post_type=gym_trainer&#038;p=3057',0,'gym_trainer','',0),(3060,2,'2018-01-25 03:00:02','2018-01-25 03:00:02','Seanmichael is an international performance artist with a penchant for rotational inertia and a rebellious attitude toward gravity. With an ethereal movement quality and otherworldly command of rigid aerial apparatuses like pole and cube, his work has been described by humans as “extraterrestrial ballet” and by extraterrestrials as “not too bad.” Seanmichael has been a stage explorer for more than 27 years with recent notable engagements including an aerial performance in Britney Spears\' music video \"Make Me,\" performing alongside famed DJ, Moby, a residency at The Galaxy Resort in Macau, and as a principle cast member in The Vespertine Circus, in San Francisco. He is a founding member of Flux Vertical Theater and Manarchy Male Revue.\n\nPersonal site: https://www.seanmichaelpolaris.com/','Sean Michael Rau','','inherit','closed','closed','','3048-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-25 03:00:02','2018-01-25 03:00:02','',3048,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3048-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3061,2,'2018-01-25 03:11:40','2018-01-25 03:11:40','Andrey Pfening was born on March 11th, 1990 in Samarkand, Uzbekistan. He spent his childhood in Samara, Russia, and at the age of 12 moved to US and has resided in San Francisco Bay Area ever since.\n\nWhile in high school, Andrey came across a youtube video of David Belle (co-founder of parkour) and instantly was drawn to the activity and began seeking out knowledge and experience. He practiced with friends and then dedicated himself to training on his own several days a week. As he gained proficiency, others were drawn to his abilities and in turn attracted to his teachings.\nAndrey has become a recognizable member of the parkour community. He helps orchestrate local monthly jams in San Francisco and is committed to educating himself about parkour and the most effective teaching tools. He frequently attends local and national parkour summits, with well known practitioners, which review the most up to date trends in the discipline, which he implements into his teachings.\n\nAfter several years of being involved in parkour community Andrey began his teaching career at two fitness facilities, Athletic Playground and The Cave. Parkour was his main subject, and as time went on Andrey’s interests spread to handstand balancing, acrobatics, crossfit, and gymnastic strength training.\n\nOutside of the gym, Andrey spends a lot of time coming up with skill progressions, class outlines and visual aids which assist his physical and vocal style of teaching. He uses video of himself and his own students to break down skills, frame by frame.\nAnnually Andrey performs in live performances, working with local and international choreographers. In 2015 and 2016 he had a rare opportunity to be part of two SF Opera productions “The Trojans” and \"Carmen.\" He also periodically choreographs and performs pieces of his own.','Andre Pfennig','','inherit','closed','closed','','3052-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-25 03:11:40','2018-01-25 03:11:40','',3052,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3052-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3062,2,'2018-01-25 03:23:47','2018-01-25 03:23:47','Sylphie is a San Francisco based performing artist and instructor. She began her training in Vaganova Ballet at the age of three. On her pursuit for a career as a dancer, she stumbled upon circus arts through her elementary school\'s circus program, Circus Waldissima. Shortly after, she began training circus professionally at the San Francisco Circus Center under the tutelage of Elena Panova and Serchmaa Byamba, and was part of the Professional Aerial Program Created by Elena Panova in 2006. Since graduating in 2008, Sylphie has been performing and teaching internationally as a circus artist and dancer.','Sylphie Currin','','inherit','closed','closed','','3049-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-25 03:23:47','2018-01-25 03:23:47','',3049,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3049-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3063,2,'2018-01-25 03:32:21','2018-01-25 03:32:21','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3051\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-09-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Tiffany Rose Mockler San Francisco Pole and Dance Instructor\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\n\nTiffany Rose Mockler is a former National Champion for Synchronized Swimming and found Pole Dance in 2010. She has competed and performed around the world. She is the current Pole Championship Series Silver Medalist and a cast member in Tonya Kay\'s Pin Up Pole Show in Los Angeles. She is also a online instructor for Cleo\'s Rockin\' Pole and teaches in both Northern and Southern California. She loves sharing the art of Pole dance with others.','Tiffany Rose Mockler','','inherit','closed','closed','','3050-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-25 03:32:21','2018-01-25 03:32:21','',3050,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3050-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3064,2,'2018-01-25 03:39:26','2018-01-25 03:39:26','Colleen started her aerial career at the Philadelphia School of Circus Arts training fabric, rope, trapeze and lyra. Throughout her time in Philadelphia she would frequent California to train at various circus schools to broaden her scope of learning. This practice allowed her to gain versatility in her aerial movement, something she still presently values. Much like Colleen herself, her classes are playful and focus on the beauty of body movement. Having a love for performing, she structures her class in a way where students are learning fundamental aerial moves, all while gaining the confidence to turn them into sequences. Her mission as an instructor and human being is to create a judge free environment where students are excited and comfortable exploring new types of movement.','Colleen Dixon','','inherit','closed','closed','','3057-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-25 03:39:26','2018-01-25 03:39:26','',3057,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3057-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3065,2,'2018-01-25 22:57:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','closed','','','','','2018-01-25 22:57:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/?p=3065',0,'post','',0),(3066,2,'2018-01-25 23:01:39','2018-01-25 23:01:39','','IMG_7177-1 (dragged)','','inherit','open','closed','','img_7177-1-dragged','','','2018-01-25 23:01:39','2018-01-25 23:01:39','',2629,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff',0,'attachment','image/tiff',0),(3067,2,'2018-01-25 23:03:19','2018-01-25 23:03:19','','Screen Shot 2018-01-25 at 3.02.52 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2018-01-25-at-3-02-52-pm','','','2018-01-25 23:03:36','2018-01-25 23:03:36','',2629,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-3.02.52-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3068,2,'2018-01-25 23:03:24','2018-01-25 23:03:24','','Screen Shot 2018-01-25 at 3.02.33 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2018-01-25-at-3-02-33-pm','','','2018-01-25 23:03:24','2018-01-25 23:03:24','',2629,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-3.02.33-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3069,2,'2018-01-25 23:04:04','2018-01-25 23:04:04','<a href=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3066\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /> <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3068\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-3.02.33-PM-201x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"201\" height=\"300\" /></a><a href=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff\">     <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3067\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-3.02.52-PM-210x300.png\" alt=\"what to wear to pole class\" width=\"210\" height=\"300\" /> </a>\r\n\r\n<span>The number one question new students ask before coming to San Francisco Pole and Dance, is </span><i><span>What should I wear for pole class!?</span></i>\r\n\r\nIn a pole dance class, skin is essential for gripping the pole. Fabrics are slippy and extremely difficult to climb in.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The essential clothing pieces for female identifying students include:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1. Tank top. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You may end up taking this off but for many, it’s nice to feel a bit more covered (and less cold) at least until you start sweating during the warm up. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2. Sports bra. Once you\'ve started sweating, and begin to practice the conditioning portion of the workout, you may want to have your side body exposed so that you can more effectively work on armpit holds and inversion prep positions while standing on the ground. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3. Shorts (the shorter the better!) </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Foundations level students will try their hand at climbing for the first time. Having skin exposed to help you grip the pole so that you can try climbing.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4. Barefeet. Pole dancing is hard, but it is even harder from a technical perspective when you add in 5-8 inch stilettos. While you are allowed to wear high heels, we recommend going barefoot until the foundational movements feel good on your body. </span>\r\n\r\n5. *Optional* Knee pads and legwarmers. For dance style classes where students will want to be able to slide along the floor, kneepads and legwarmers are recommended. If you don\'t have any, we have two styles for sale at the studio.\r\n\r\nFor male-identifying students, shorts in a brief style are recommended. Having the skin of the upper thighs is important for pole sits and other moves that get a bit crotchy!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ: What should I wear to pole class?','','inherit','closed','closed','','2629-revision-v1','','','2018-01-25 23:04:04','2018-01-25 23:04:04','',2629,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/2629-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3070,2,'2018-01-25 23:05:35','2018-01-25 23:05:35','<a href=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3066\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /> <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3068\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-3.02.33-PM-201x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"201\" height=\"300\" /></a><a href=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_7177-1-dragged.tiff\">     <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3067\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-3.02.52-PM-210x300.png\" alt=\"what to wear to pole class\" width=\"210\" height=\"300\" /> </a>\r\n\r\nThe number one question new students ask before coming to San Francisco Pole and Dance, is <i>What should I wear for pole class!?</i>\r\n\r\nIn a pole dance class, skin is essential for gripping the pole. Fabrics are slippy and extremely difficult to climb in.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The essential clothing pieces for female identifying students include:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1. Tank top or T-shirt. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You\'ll likely end up taking this off but for many, it’s nice to feel a bit more covered (and less cold) at least until you start sweating during the warm up. And if you don\'t want your belly exposed, you can keep it on!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2. Sports bra. Once you\'ve started sweating, and begin to practice the conditioning portion of the workout, you may want to have your side body exposed so that you can more effectively work on armpit holds and inversion prep positions while standing on the ground. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3. Shorts (the shorter the better!) </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Foundations level students will try their hand at climbing for the first time. Having skin exposed to help you grip the pole so that you can try climbing.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4. Barefeet. Pole dancing is hard, but it is even harder from a technical perspective when you add in 5-8 inch stilettos. While you are allowed to wear high heels, we recommend going barefoot until the foundational movements feel good on your body. </span>\r\n\r\n5. *Optional* Knee pads and legwarmers. For dance style classes where students will want to be able to slide along the floor, kneepads and legwarmers are recommended. If you don\'t have any, we have two styles for sale at the studio.\r\n\r\nFor male-identifying students, shorts in a brief style are recommended. Having the skin of the upper thighs is important for pole sits and other moves that get a bit crotchy!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ: What should I wear to pole class?','','inherit','closed','closed','','2629-revision-v1','','','2018-01-25 23:05:35','2018-01-25 23:05:35','',2629,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/2629-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3071,2,'2018-01-26 00:13:01','2018-01-26 00:13:01','','Screen Shot 2018-01-25 at 4.12.40 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2018-01-25-at-4-12-40-pm','','','2018-01-26 00:13:18','2018-01-26 00:13:18','',2980,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-4.12.40-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3072,2,'2018-01-26 00:13:27','2018-01-26 00:13:27','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3071\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Screen-Shot-2018-01-25-at-4.12.40-PM.png\" alt=\"pole dance move inside leg hang #pdinsideleghang gemini scorpio\" width=\"198\" height=\"220\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This month’s move of the month is inside leg hang, also known as scorpio or gemini. You can search Instagram for variations of this move by searching #pdinsideleghang #pdgemini or #pdscorpio</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Check out a <a href=\"https://youtu.be/VENN80am4GE\">video</a> of instructor Amy, performing the basic instruction for an outside leg hang. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A couple of things to note:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As you perform your inversion, you should keep your outside hand on top, but no higher than your eyebrows. A lot of beginners have a tendency to reach too high, which actually makes this move harder to nail. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you’ve performed your inversion, lift your hips up so that you don’t get your top hand stuck under your leg on the pole. The hip lift helps get your hips over your hand so that you can drop your hand in an elegant and clean manner.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aim to straighten your back leg as far back behind you and as straight as possible. May beginner level students have a tendency to leave that back leg too high in the air. If you pretend like you are trying to prance your back leg to the ground with a straight knee and a pointed toe, you will be more likely to keep your lines clean, sharp, and most importantly, safe! You\'ll also be able to start exploring your range of motion through your back leg and may even surprise yourself with how far down you can reach it!</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Note that as we work on this move over the next month, we’d love to see your variations and artistic flair added to it! Tag #sfpoleanddance in your videos so that we can share variations and work on inside leg hang together! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next month, we’ll post a round up of all the cool variations that you share!</span>','Pole Trick of the Month: Inside Leg Hang/Gemini, i.e. #pdinsideleghang','','inherit','closed','closed','','2980-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 00:13:27','2018-01-26 00:13:27','',2980,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/2980-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(3073,2,'2018-01-26 21:21:44','2018-01-26 21:21:44','<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3055\" src=\"http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2017-12-29-SFPD-Headshots-03-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Joshua Aurora San Francisco Pole and Dance instructor\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nAurora has studied dance, yoga, and martial arts for most of their life. Aurora trained in ballet, jazz, and contemporary dance including summer programs with the Northern California Ballet and California State Summer School for the Arts. Aurora started teaching yoga and dance when they were 18 and has continued to do so intermittently for the last ten years while running an acupuncture, meditation, and energy healing practice. They also return frequently to their home dance studio in South Lake Tahoe to teach young dancers safe alignment, tricks, and AcroYoga. Aurora performs neo burlesque and pole in the Bay Area.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Josh/Aurora','','inherit','closed','closed','','3054-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-26 21:21:44','2018-01-26 21:21:44','',3054,'http://past-lobster.flywheelsites.com/3054-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
